---------------------------

## Issue

I got ReferenceError while I was trying migrate the contract. 

I have got Wallet.sol for ERC20 wallet contract and Tokens.sol testing wallet with sample token with its constructor as : 

```
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

import "../node_modules/@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol";

contract Link is ERC20 {
    constructor() ERC20("Chainlink", "LINK") public {
        _mint(msg.sender, 1000);
    }
}
```

2_wallet_migration.js:

```
const Migrations = artifacts.require("Wallet");

module.exports = function (deployer) {
  deployer.deploy(Wallet);
};
```


3_tokens_migration.js:

```
const Migrations = artifacts.require("Link");

module.exports = function (deployer) {
  deployer.deploy(Link);
};
```
## Error
2_wallet_migration.js
=====================

ReferenceError: Wallet is not defined
    at module.exports (/home/eba/authic/ethereum-201/eba-dex/migrations/2_wallet_migration.js:4:19)
    at Migration._load (/usr/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/migrate/Migration.js:53:1)
    at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)
    at Migration.run (/usr/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/migrate/Migration.js:202:1)
